--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INFORMATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This file lists changes made to the Ansible role. It follows semantic versioning
guidelines. The content is sorted in reverse chronological order and formatted
to allow easy grepping by scripts.

The fields are:
B: bug
C: change
E: enhancement
F: feature

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Version 6.3.0 (2020-12-31)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.2-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 12.1-RELEASE

* Version 6.2.3 (2020-12-20)
E: Modify 'textfile_collector' path to comply with BSD directory structure

* Version 6.2.2 (2020-10-30)
E: Simplify Ansible file header (ansible_managed)

* Version 6.2.1 (2020-08-18)
B: Fix echo commands (BSD echo does not support backslash character sequences)

* Version 6.2.0 (2020-07-24)
F: Add script 'zfs_trim-pools' to trim ZFS pools

* Version 6.1.0 (2020-07-03)
F: Add support for monitoring via Prometheus node_exporter (textfile_collector)

* Version 6.0.0 (2020-07-03)
C: Redesign cron tasks (use Ansible cron module)
C: Remove option 'zfs_check_pools_interval'
C: Add option 'zfs_check_pools_minute' to specify interval (Default: '*/15')

* Version 5.0.0 (2020-07-02)
C: Move scripts to '/usr/local/sbin'
E: Remove 'common' role dependency

* Version 4.2.0 (2019-11-08)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.1-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE

* Version 4.1.0 (2019-05-26)
F: Port role to Ansible 2.8

* Version 4.0.0 (2019-01-24)
C: Rename option 'zfs_monitor_mail_recipient' to 'zfs_monitor_mail_from_address'
C: Rename option 'zfs_monitor_mail_sender' to 'zfs_monitor_mail_to_address'

* Version 3.0.1 (2019-01-22)
E: Improve script by throwing error message if script is executed interactively

* Version 3.0.0 (2019-01-22)
C: Rename option 'zfs_pools' to 'zfs_scrub_pools_pools'
C: Rename option 'zfs_scrub_pools_cron_hour' to 'zfs_scrub_pools_hour'
C: Rename option 'zfs_scrub_pools_cron_minute' to 'zfs_scrub_pools_minute'
C: Rename option 'zfs_scrub_pools_cron_weekday' to 'zfs_scrub_pools_weekday'
F: Add 'zfs_check-pool' script and configuration options
E: Improve parameters and update documentation

* Version 2.4.1 (2019-01-21)
E: Improve script and reduce noise by removing echo command from alerting function

* Version 2.4.0 (2019-01-13)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 11.2-RELEASE

* Version 2.3.9 (2019-01-09)
B: Fix issue introduced with improvements to prevent globbing and word splitting

* Version 2.3.8 (2019-01-09)
E: Improve Shell script to prevent globbing and word splitting

* Version 2.3.7 (2018-12-15)
E: Minor style improvement

* Version 2.3.6 (2018-12-10)
E: Change 'mailx' command for non FreeBSD systems

* Version 2.3.5 (2018-12-07)
E: Remove 'zfs_monitor_mail_subject' parameter

* Version 2.3.4 (2018-12-07)
E: Remove email information from message

* Version 2.3.3 (2018-10-20)
E: Update support information of OpenBSD

* Version 2.3.2 (2018-07-19)
E: Shell script improvements

* Version 2.3.1 (2018-07-12)
E: Generate a random minute for the cronjob

* Version 2.3.0 (2018-07-01)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 11.2-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 11.1-RELEASE

* Version 2.2.0 (2018-05-22)
F: Port role to Ansible 2.5

* Version 2.1.2 (2018-04-24)
E: Simplify role by removing 'template' option

* Version 2.1.1 (2018-04-04)
E: Update support information of OpenBSD

* Version 2.1.0 (2018-03-30)
F: Port role to Ansible 2.4

* Version 2.0.1 (2018-02-24)
B: Correct term in state filter

* Version 2.0.0 (2018-02-20)
E: Simplify and improve Ansible role

* Version 1.1.1 (2017-10-18)
E: Update support information of OpenBSD

* Version 1.1.0 (2017-08-26)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 11.1-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 11.0-RELEASE

* Version 1.0.0 (2017-08-01)
E: Stabilize, improve and cleanup Ansible role

* Version 0.5.1 (2017-04-16)
E: Update support information of OpenBSD

* Version 0.5.0 (2016-10-14)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 11.0-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 10.3-RELEASE

* Version 0.4.2 (2016-09-03)
E: Update support information of OpenBSD

* Version 0.4.1 (2016-05-29)
E: Improve FreeBSD support

* Version 0.4.0 (2016-05-21)
C: Add support for Ansible 2.0

* Version 0.3.0 (2016-04-09)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 10.3-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 10.2-RELEASE

* Version 0.2.2 (2016-04-02)
E: Update support information for OpenBSD 5.9

* Version 0.2.1 (2016-03-08)
E: Minor script improvements

* Version 0.2.0 (2016-01-21)
C: Drop support for OS family 'Gentoo'

* Version 0.1.4 (2015-11-17)
E: Add missing Ansible tags

* Version 0.1.3 (2015-08-23)
E: Improve Shell exit codes

* Version 0.1.2 (2015-03-05)
E: Minor script improvements

* Version 0.1.1 (2015-02-03)
